- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper deals with quantum process algebras and introduces schedulers to solve nondeterministic choices. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possibility because quantum computing is an emerging technology and the paper deals with quantum processes. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possibility because the paper proposes definitions of schedulers and investigates their relation to observational equivalence, which could be relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility because quantum computing is related to computational complexity, but it is less likely than the other categories listed.
